If you read greentexts or real anecdotes of people claiming they encountered bigfoot, a skinwalker, whatever monster in the wilderness, even though it seems they get overtaken by pure instinct and start running/fighting/moving/etc. as a reflex, the way they claim to experience...

It is the "emotional" part of their brain shutting down and being overtaken by what seems like not instinct or panic, but pure reason and logical thinking. It reminds me of what Heidegger seems to say about "being here" being somewhat defined by "practicality" and individuality.

A bigger Heidegger reader could say it better. It's also very illustrative of what Contrary Pancake said about people saying you must have "blind confidence" being itself result from the guilt of overthinking. People who possess blind confidence never perceive themselves that way
